http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Hyderabad/KCR-sets-the-ball-rolling-for-Pharma-City/article14014728.ece

Chief Minister K. Chandrasekhar Rao has directed the authorities of the Industries Department to prepare a detailed project report (DPR) for the proposed Pharma City in Mucherla area of Ranga Reddy district.The Centre has already announced that it would consider the Pharma City being proposed by the Government of Telangana under its National Investment and Manufacturing Zones (NIMZs) scheme. The Pharma City is expected to come up in about 12,000 acres, out of which over 2,000 acres has already been identified for acquisition.The State Government is planning to develop the Pharma City with international standards with zero liquid waste.The Chief Minister has asked the officials to take proper measures for treatment of waste generated in the pharmaceutical units in the Pharma City by studying the management systems being implemented in the US, Europe and Japan.A team led by Additional Secretary in the Chief Minsterâ€™s office A. Shanti Kumari would soon be sent to such countries to design the Pharma City with international standards.